properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 5 at 6:59PM PST until February 7 at 4:23AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a flood warning
for the following rivers in Washington...

Issaquah Creek Near Issaquah affecting King County


Moderate to locally heavy rainfall will continue at times through
early Friday. This will cause the Issaquah Creek to rise above flood
stage after midnight tonight.

The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a

* Flood Warning for
The Issaquah Creek Near Issaquah
* from late tonight to late Thursday night.
* At  5:15 PM Wednesday the flow was 1577 cfs.
* Flood flow is 2000 cfs.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will rise above flood flow around 2 AM
Thursday and crest near 2127 cfs around 4 PM Thursday. The river
will fall below flood flow Thursday evening.
* Impact...At 2000 cfs, Issaquah Creek will flood most low areas in
the valley. Swift waters will flood residential and business areas
and roads including Newport Way.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
